FBIS4-402 "drafr069_a_94036" FBIS-AFR-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Medecins Sans Frontieres Evacuating Belgian Staff Medecins Sans Frontieres Evacuating Belgian Staff LD1004122094 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1100 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004122094 Brussels La Une Radio Network French BFN [Text] Medecins Sans Frontieres has decided to evacuate all its Belgian staff now in Rwanda in light of the anti-Belgian feeling reigning in the country. Medecins Sans Frontieres officials said that the decision was made because of the evolution of the situation in Rwanda. The humanitarian organization added that, if circumstances allow, Belgian staff will be replaced by medical staff of other nationalities.
